37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.04d8da43-39b7-4ae8-bb8f-fa47bffe8921.prompt=Please Enter groupDN to Start Search Parent Groups\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.15e296f1-84ec-4867-a88c-294af2521dac.prompt=Please Enter Active Directory Username\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.58f28456-d274-4de7-807b-4a273f54e1f4.prompt=Please Enter groupDN to Start Search Parent Groups\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.716269ac-45eb-4a76-8720-0b32938a70f9.prompt=Please Enter Active Directory Domain Controller Host\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.7689c02b-8bad-4549-9922-52a1481a6425.description=
Iterates through a list of values. Modifying the value of the list and delimiter inputs during iteration is not generally supported.

Inputs\:
list - The list to iterate through.
separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.
failure - failed to process the list.

Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously.

WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.
37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.7737071c-2967-4497-820e-8f32af9f0e5e.description=
Gets the string value of an LDAP objects named property.
Creates a collection if more than one property of the same name exists.
Continue to call this same operation for all values until No More Values is returned.

Input Parameters\:
host - Name or IP address of LDAP server to query.
DN - DN of object to get property.
propertyName - Name of property to get.
username - Name of user to connect to LDAP as.
password - Password of user.
useADAuth - Add this input and set to false if using a non AD LDAP server. If false, uses ServerBind instead of secure NTLM based bind.
port - Specify the port in case it is not the default one, or it is not specified in the host path.

Responses\:
value retrieved - The value was retrieved and set as the result (returnResult).
no more values - There are no more values in the collection.
failure - failed to complete operation (one of the reasons could be port validation failure).
37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.865cc629-ef26-4d2c-87bd-471eb6f83693.prompt=Alternate Credentials - UserName\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.8bdfc3cc-309b-443e-9ee1-772ed2833e6e.prompt=Please Enter Active Directory Host\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.8c0de564-c6e9-4c94-bb4c-e282e8ea6f4d.prompt=Please Enter a groupDN to Find\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.8c818d57-219a-4496-bf70-382313ef1d0c.prompt=Please Enter Active Direcotry Password\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.9922b958-54d2-4c93-b6a7-5c12d8ab7767.description=
Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

If the matchType is RegEx, input matchTo is the regular expression like \: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. Input toMatch is the actual string to check to see if it matches the matchTo expression.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against. 
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.
37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.9dc9dc45-70ea-4fbb-a119-842851d5ff41.prompt=Please Enter Active Direcotry Password\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.9e215250-4619-444d-8f12-8aaf4ce90d97.prompt=Enter a value for String1 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.a001697d-f31f-4de1-8069-3da18749ce6b.description=
Compares two strings lexigraphically.

Inputs\:
String1 - The first string.
String2 - The string to compare string 1 to.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true' then the compare is not case sensitive.

responses\:
before - If string 1 is alphabetically before string 2.
after - If string 1 is alphabetically after string 2.
same - If string 1 is alphabetically equal to string 2.
failure - If Something goes wrong.
37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.b8dd8cda-215b-48d6-a3f3-7c69f02fc103.prompt=Enter a value for String2 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.c962a43b-2363-4ca9-83b4-1de274878aad.prompt=Alternate Credentials - Password\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.ca281010-25cd-430e-86e3-47a0f15b16d2.prompt=Distinguished Name\: 37207842-c866-4078-9aca-6e7e9a959e98.description=
The flow will  find a group (groupDNToFind) in a group (groupDNToStart)'s parent groups recursively. For example, OODevSubGroup2 is a member of OODevSubGroup1. OODevSubGroup1 is a member of OODevGroup. It should be able to find OODevGroup in OODevSubGroup2's parent groups. It is intended to be used as a sub flow for "Is User in Group".

Inputs\:
host - The hostname of an Active Directory domain controller.
username - The username for host.
password - The password for the username.
groupDNToFind - The DN of the group to find, for example \: CN\=OODevGroup,OU\=OODevTest,DC\=battleground,DC\=ad.
groupDNToStart - The DN of the group to search for its parent groups, for example\: CN\=OODevSubGroup2,OU\=OODevTest,DC\=battleground,DC\=ad.

Responses\:
success - The groupDNToFind is one of the parent groups of the groupDNToStart.
failure - The groupDNToFind is not one of the parent groups of the groupDNToStart.
